Deploy AWS Lambda functions using embedded artifacts.

Usage:
  lambda
      Deploy all embedded Lambda functions with default configuration.

  lambda --name <function> [--memory <mb>] [--timeout <seconds>]
      Deploy a specific Lambda function with optional memory and timeout settings.

Flags:
  --name       Lambda function name (omit to deploy all embedded functions)
  --memory     Memory size in MB (default: 128)
  --timeout    Timeout in seconds (default: 10)

Examples:
  lambda --name firehose-router
  lambda --name processing-controller --memory 256 --timeout 15
  lambda

Note:
  ZIP artifacts are embedded in the CLI and automatically uploaded to S3 during deployment.
  To see a list of available Lambda artifacts, run: artifacts
